title: The fable of the dog and the bone
Sanson and Dalila
description: A work that focuses on the biblical story of Samson, the man whose strength came from his hair (custom of his religion), and Dalida the beautiful woman of another culture and totally seductive. The author shows a fairly detailed version of the fact that includes elements inherent in the story.

title: Leda col cigno
description: "Leda col cigno" is another work of the painter inspired by Greek mythology, portrays in a very subtle way the romance or the seduction of Zeus, in the form of a swan, to the beautiful Leda.

title: Spring
description: Beautiful and cheerful picture that illustrates the joy of the primvera, in the same predominates the yellow color.

title: The dream of Jacob
description: This work gives us a fragment of the biblical story of one of the patriarchs of the faith, Jacob, inspired by an oil painting by the Spanish Baroque painter José de Ribera, dated 1639 named in the same way "The dream of Jacob". From where Gabino takes the image of Jacob, but to which he adds his dream in itself: angels descending from heaven to earth.

title: The Tempest
description:
A work that shows sweetness and vulnerability, purity and destruction. The Tempest is part of the collection of works that have the measures: 122 x 195.
Newly the brushstroke of the artist plays between subtlety and perfectionism.

title: The agreement
description: A work that shows the beauty of the woman in well-detailed nudes, the painter Gabino Amaya Cacho puts special emphasis on the expressions of the face, details of the hands and joviality of the skin.

title: Las Tres Gracias "The Three Graces"
description: Another mythological work of the painter Gabino Amaya Cacho, and probably one of the most appreciated of the painter. The three Graces, daughters of Zeus and goddesses of the spell, joy and beauty, add these characteristics in a painting painted under natural light and without any human model. Is an innovative proposal in contrast to the different paintings made in the past. The painter drew well-defined lines of human physiognomy from his imagination.

title: The Ages of Bacchus
description: Inspired by classical mythology, Gabino Amaya Cacho illustrates Bacchus (Dionysus), god of wine in a very suggestive and striking work.

title: Icarus and Daedalus
description: Icarus and Daedalus is one of the best quoted works of the Spanish painter Gabino Amaya Cacho. Inspired by Greek mythology, Gabino illustrates his point of view of history detailing each of the characters. Icarus, the young man who falls from the sky, Daedalus, his father.

description:
The combination of overlapping points illuminated with live acrylics allows us to enjoy a cheerful and daring composition.
A true work of art by the pioneer of Abstract Pointillism, Gabino Amaya Cacho.
